            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1846-06-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1846-06-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="136" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d136">
                <head>No. 5.</head>
                <dateline>[<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian" when="1846-06-12">June 12,
                            1846</date>]</dateline>
                <p rend="center">PROPOSED AMENDMENT OF ARTICLE II OF TREATY.</p>
                <p>The following was moved in the Senate of the United States, on 12th June,
                            1846, as an addition to the Resolution advising the President to accept
                            the proposal:</p>
                <p>With the following proviso at the end of the second Article of the
                            proposed Convention, to wit:</p>
                <p>“<hi rend="italic">Provided</hi>, That the right of navigating the
                            Columbia River secured to the Hudson’s Bay Company, and to all British
                            subjects trading with the same, he limited to the year A. D. 1863, when
                            it shall cease and determine.”</p>
            </div>
